<a name="Emacs-GnuTLS"></a>
<h1 class="top">Emacs GnuTLS</h1>
<p>This manual describes the Emacs GnuTLS integration.
</p>
<p>GnuTLS is a library that establishes encrypted <acronym>SSL</acronym> or
<acronym>TLS</acronym> connections.  Emacs supports it through the
<samp>gnutls.c</samp> and <samp>gnutls.h</samp> C files and the <samp>gnutls.el</samp>
Emacs Lisp library.
</p>
<p>This file describes the Emacs GnuTLS integration.
</p>
