<a name="Overview-1"></a>
<h2 class="chapter">1 Overview</h2>

<p>The GnuTLS library is an optional add-on for Emacs.  Through it, any
Emacs Lisp program can establish encrypted network connections that
use <em>Secure Socket Layer</em> (<acronym>SSL</acronym>) and <em>Transport Layer
Security</em> (<acronym>TLS</acronym>) protocols.  The process of using
<acronym>SSL</acronym> and <acronym>TLS</acronym> in establishing connections is as
automated and transparent as possible.
</p>
<p>The user has only a few customization options currently: the log
level, priority string, trustfile list, and the minimum number of bits
to be used in Diffie-Hellman key exchange.  Rumors that every Emacs
library requires at least 83 customizable variables are thus proven
false.
</p>
<hr>
